# ElevenLabs Scribe API key — used for transcription / segment identification.
# Get one at https://elevenlabs.io (the same key the video-use skill uses).
# Easiest way to set it: the panel's settings (gear icon > ElevenLabs > Add API key)
# writes it here for you. Every setting below is also editable from the panel's
# settings > Advanced accordion.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
EDITAGENT_AI_TIMEOUT_MS=900000
# Note: the "AI analysis" (retake keep/cut, silence threshold) is done by Claude
# itself on your Claude *subscription* — no separate AI API key or credits. With
# "Sync with Claude Code" ON it runs via MCP tools in your chat; OFF (default) the
# panel runs `claude` headlessly for you (see the Panel AI section below).
#
# The Remove Silences tab is loudness-based (ffmpeg only): it needs NO API key
# and no transcription — so it works even without ELEVENLABS_API_KEY set.

# Optional: bridge port shared by the MCP server and the Premiere panel.
# Default 3001. If you change it, the panel auto-reads the negotiated port
# from ~/.editagent/bridge-port, so you normally don't need to touch the panel.
# PREMIERE_BRIDGE_PORT=3001

# Optional: override the transcript cache directory (default: <project>/.cache).
# EDITAGENT_CACHE_DIR=

# Optional: path to ffmpeg if not on PATH.
# FFMPEG_BIN=ffmpeg

# Transcription is scoped to what's ON THE TIMELINE (only the used clip source ranges
# go to ElevenLabs Scribe — off-timeline footage is never billed; a reload after cutting
# reuses a union cache and re-bills nothing). These tune how the used ranges are grouped
# into the few continuous "islands" that get transcribed:
#   MERGE_GAP — coalesce ranges closer than this many seconds into one island (bigger =
#   fewer Scribe calls but re-includes more in-between audio; default 2).
#   PAD — seconds of context kept on each island edge so edge words aren't clipped (default 0.25).
# EDITAGENT_TRANSCRIBE_MERGE_GAP=2
# EDITAGENT_TRANSCRIBE_PAD=0.25

# ElevenLabs speech-to-text model (the panel's Transcription dropdown overrides this)
# and the list price per audio hour used for the AI usage log's cost estimates.
# EDITAGENT_SCRIBE_MODEL=scribe_v2
# EDITAGENT_SCRIBE_RATE=0.22

# ── Fast Apply All (XML rebuild) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ripple applies with at least this many cuts skip in-place razoring and build
# the tightened sequence as FCP7 XML instead (seconds vs minutes). 0 disables.
# EDITAGENT_REBUILD_MIN=100
# The rebuild ROUND-TRIPS Premiere's own XML export (effects/transforms/audio
# levels/transitions that FCP7 XML carries survive the apply). Set to 0 to skip
# the round-trip and use the bare generated rebuild (drops effects).
# EDITAGENT_ROUNDTRIP=1

# ── Panel AI actions ("Calculate by AI" / "Analyze w/ Claude") ───────────────
# With "Sync with Claude Code" OFF (the default), these buttons run the `claude`
# CLI HEADLESSLY on your Claude *subscription* (keychain login — no API key, no
# extra credits) so you never have to type a prompt in chat. The panel's
# Model/Effort dropdowns set these per call; the values below are only fallback
# defaults used when the panel doesn't send them.
#
# Model: "latest" (your Claude Code default) or an alias: opus / sonnet / haiku / fable.
# EDITAGENT_AI_MODEL=latest
# Effort: low | medium | high | xhigh | max.
# EDITAGENT_AI_EFFORT=high
# Hard timeout for one headless call, ms (default 600000 = 10 min). Raise it for
# big retake analyses on Opus/Max over a long transcript.
# EDITAGENT_AI_TIMEOUT_MS=900000
# Full path to `claude` if it isn't auto-found (we try this, then ~/.local/bin/claude,
# /usr/local/bin, /opt/homebrew/bin, then PATH).
# EDITAGENT_CLAUDE_BIN=/Users/you/.local/bin/claude
# If you keep multiple Claude Code logins in separate config folders (via
# CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR), point the AI calls at the one to use. Without this, a
# panel-started server uses the DEFAULT ~/.claude login, which can be stale
# ("OAuth session expired") if you only ever sign in to a custom folder.
# EDITAGENT_CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=/Users/you/.claude-personal
#
# Auth: the headless call reuses your existing `claude` login and scrubs
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY so it never silently bills a pay-per-token key. On a headless
# box with no keychain, run `claude setup-token` and export CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloud vs Self-hosted mode
# The panel now defaults to CLOUD mode: AI, transcription and the animation
# agent run through the OpenCutAgent backend on your Google-linked account (no
# keys, no Claude install needed). Toggle "Self-hosted" in the panel settings
# to run fully locally with the options above instead. The mode itself is
# stored per machine in ~/.opencutagent/cloud.json, not here.
# Where the cloud service lives; point at your own deployment of backend/
# (http://localhost:3000 while developing it).
# EDITAGENT_CLOUD_URL=https://cloud.opencutagent.com
